function: registernode Register a server in the directory server
prm nodename: URL of the server
prm success: true if OK
prm msg: Error message

function: nodelogout End the session with the directory server
prm session: Session ID obtained from nodelogin

function: nodelogin Starts a session with the directory server
prm nodename: URL of the server
prm session: Session ID used for API requests

function: nodepass Second step of the nodelogin operation
	The client does not provide a password, but must return the session and the signature
	computed using its system key.
prm session: Session ID obtained from nodelogin
prm sign: Signature of the session ID done using the client system key

function: publish (deprecate see publish_v2) Add or update public information about one user of the client server
prm session: Session ID
prm info: Information about one user

function: publish_v2 Add or update public information about one user of the client server
prm session: Session ID
prm info: Information about one user

function: publish_file Record the content of a user photo.
	The file is sent in multiple chunks. All chunks are appended to a temporary file.
	The temporary file is committed when more == false.
prm session: Session ID
prm user: User nick name
prm name: File name. either photo.jpg or mini-photo.jpg
prm content: File content (potentially partial)
prm more: The content is incomplete, more calls to publish_file are expected
prm append: This is not the first call to publish_file, the content must be appended to the already received content.

function: remove Remove all the content of a user, received by the publish_v2 and publish_file functions.
prm session:
prm user: User nick name

function: recordemail Associate a user and email to a node in the directory server
prm session: Session ID
prm userid: User nick name
prm email: Email of the user

function: deleteemail Remove a user and email from a node in the directory server
prm session: Session ID
prm userid: User nick name
prm email: Email of the user

